Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
gui_ungroup_hinst(25.10)                              gui_ungroup_hinst(25.10)

Name
       gui_ungroup_hinst  -  Displays  the submodules for the specified module
       guide

Syntax
       gui_ungroup_hinst

       [-help]

       [-display_all_constraints]

       [-type {<flex_model>} | <hname>]

       Displays the submodules for the specified  module  guide.  The  gui_un-
       group_hinst  command  is equivalent to the Ungroup widget  on the tool-
       bar.

       If you try to ungroup a module that contains only  standard  cells  and
       marcos  but  does  not contain any submodules, the tool ignores the un-
       group request and issues the following warning:

       **WARN:       (ENCSYT-3162):        Cannot        ungroup        Module
       'DTMF_INST/RAM_128x16_TEST_INST' because it has no child.

Parameters
       -help  Prints a brief description that includes type and default infor-
              mation for each gui_ungroup_hinst parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man gui_ungroup_hinst

       -display_all_constraints
              Displays  all  constraints, such as fences, guides, regions, and
              soft guides, regardless of the current hierarchy. When this  op-
              tion is specified, you can view the child constraints.

       <hname>
              Specifies  the  name  of the hierarchical instance (hinst) to be
              ungrouped.

       -type {<flex_model>}
              Specifies the object type to be ungrouped.  At present, only the
              flex_model type is supported.

              If you specify -type {<flex_model>}, the  command  ungroups  all
              hierarchical  instances  or parent hinst down to the flex_module
              and/or flex_instgroup level.

Examples
              * The following command ungroups the specified module  and  dis-
                plays its submodules.

                gui_ungroup_hinst DTMF_INST/TDSP_CORE_INST

              * The  following  command ungroups all hierarchical instances or
                parent hinst down to  the  flex_module  and/or  flex_instgroup
                level:

                gui_ungroup_hinst -type {<flex_model>}

